docs.abstract: A Brexit deal looks possible, and China trade tensions eased slightly. That probably will not stop the Federal Reserve from cutting rates again this month.
docs.snippet: A Brexit deal looks possible, and China trade tensions eased slightly. That probably will not stop the Federal Reserve from cutting rates again this month.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The United Kingdom drew closer this week to exiting the European Union with a deal, and trade talks with China have led to a mild de-escalation. But those hopeful signs were not enough to soothe Federal Reserve officials’ worries about the United States economy.

headline.main: Fed Signals a Rate Cut Remains Possible, Despite Glimmers of Economic Hope
headline.print_headline: Fed Signals That a Rate Cut Remains Possible
